The President of the United States issued a statement on World Malaria Day, expressing the commitment to make the US a leader in ending deaths from malaria by 2015. The focus is on ending malaria as a major public health threat in Africa, where it kills nearly one million people each year. Progress has been made in providing bed nets and anti-malarial drugs to communities, and there is optimism that ambitious goals can be achieved. The statement also emphasizes the importance of investing in health systems and working with partners to address other global health threats. The President reiterates the commitment to work with partners in the fight against malaria.